  • Classes in docreader.list used by docreader.list 
    Class and Description
    ListReader
    Full featured ListReader which takes care of independent multilevel lists, pseudo consecutive lists, pseudo / fake list paragraphs and other such niceties.
    ListReader.FakeLsidManager
    Manages crafted List-IDs necessary for paragraphs which are technically not in a list but need to behave as if they were Note: There should be only one instance of this class for each document
    ListReader.SublistStack
    Manages a stack of all our sublist managers; will grow larger for lists nested in tables
    ListReaderPlain
    Computes the number text which prepends each list paragraph Note: This class only handles the raw number text and does not apply any further formatting as described in [MS-DOC], v20140721, 2.4.6.3, Part 3 to it.
    ListReaderPlain.LevelTuple
    Storage for a particular level of a particular list in the document
    ListReaderPlain.LevelTuple.BaseData 
    ListReaderPlain.LevelTuple.LvlData 
    ListReaderPlain.LevelTupleReadOnly
    Storage for a particular level of a particular list in the document, immutable version with ListFormatOverrideLevels resolved
    ListReaderPlain.ListStore
    Storage for all lists in the document
    ListReaderPlain.ListStore.LevelStore
    Storage for a particular list in the document (i.e. there is one instance of this class for each lsid)
    NestingType
    Different types of nested structures
    SublistManager
    Determines the fully qualified identifier for a list-item and takes care about correct parent/child-relationships
    SublistManager.FakeListManager
    Handles paragraphs which are technically not in a list but visually look like a list member
    i.e.
    SublistManager.LevelStore
    Stores a list in a document
    SublistManager.LevelStore.LevelTuple
    Stores levels of a list
    SublistManager.LevelStore.LevelTuple.BreadcrumbData
    Store and manage the number texts of all the different sublist levels;
    not immutable
    SublistManager.LevelStore.LevelTupleA 
    SublistManager.LevelStore.LevelTupleWSkippedLevels
    immutable wrapper class for a concrete LevelTuple and an array of its associated (preceding) skipped LevelTuples
    SublistManager.LevelTupleWFakeNumberText
    Small helper class which stores a fake numberText along with a levelTuple; necessary for pseudo / fake list paragraphs
    SublistManager.ParagraphPropertiesDeterminer
    Determines formatting properties of a paragraph necessary for correct inclusion into a list hierarchy with respect to any possible list formatting overrides
    SublistManager.ParagraphPropertiesDeterminer.ListType
